cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes an opportunistic network coding scheme and derives the closed-form outage probability expression, which involves information theory concepts such as channel coding and decoding. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on cellular relay networks and proposes a fully distributed method to implement the opportunistic network coding scheme without the need for feedback between two network nodes. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed scheme involves controlling the transmission and reception of messages in a cellular relay network, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves the development and analysis of a network coding scheme for cellular relay networks, which can be considered as a computational engineering problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers the use of the proposed opportunistic network coding scheme for cellular downlink transmissions, which may involve multimedia data such as video and audio.
